## Overview

Create comprehensive CLI tests that run in CI without external dependencies. Tests verify all command-line flags and behaviors.

## Implementation

Create `tests/cli_test.rs`:

```rust
use std::process::Command;

#[test]
fn test_cli_help() {
    let output = Command::new("cargo")
        .args(["run", "--", "--help"])
        .output()
        .expect("Failed to run");

    let stdout = String::from_utf8_lossy(&output.stdout);
    assert!(stdout.contains("sage-dice"));
    assert!(stdout.contains("EXAMPLES"));
}

#[test]
fn test_cli_version() {
    let output = Command::new("cargo")
        .args(["run", "--", "--version"])
        .output()
        .expect("Failed to run");

    let stdout = String::from_utf8_lossy(&output.stdout);
    assert!(stdout.contains("0.1.0"));
}

#[test]
fn test_cli_notation_flag() {
    let output = Command::new("cargo")
        .args(["run", "--", "--notation", "d20"])
        .output()
        .expect("Failed to run");

    assert!(output.status.success());
}

#[test]
fn test_cli_seed_deterministic() {
    let output1 = Command::new("cargo")
        .args(["run", "--", "--notation", "--seed", "42", "d20"])
        .output()
        .expect("Failed to run");

    let output2 = Command::new("cargo")
        .args(["run", "--", "--notation", "--seed", "42", "d20"])
        .output()
        .expect("Failed to run");

    assert_eq!(output1.stdout, output2.stdout);
}

#[test]
fn test_cli_json_output() {
    let output = Command::new("cargo")
        .args(["run", "--", "--notation", "--json", "2d6+3"])
        .output()
        .expect("Failed to run");

    let stdout = String::from_utf8_lossy(&output.stdout);
    assert!(stdout.contains("\"notation\""));
    assert!(stdout.contains("\"total\""));
}
```

## Files to Create

- `tests/cli_test.rs` - New test file

## Dependencies

- Requires `src/main.rs` to be wired with CLI argument parsing
- Does NOT require Ollama or external services

## Success Criteria

- All tests pass with `cargo test`
- `test_cli_help` verifies help output contains description and examples
- `test_cli_version` verifies version string matches 0.1.0
- `test_cli_notation_flag` verifies --notation flag is accepted
- `test_cli_seed_deterministic` verifies same seed produces same output
- `test_cli_json_output` verifies --json flag produces valid JSON keys
- Tests are 100% CI-runnable (no external dependencies)

